projects.title: MeltShiny
projects.description: MeltShiny is a software application designed to automate the analysis and visualization of DNA melting curves, aiding researchers in chemistry, biology, and genetics. The application leverages the powerful tools MeltWin and MeltR to offer an intuitive graphical user interface combined with robust data processing capabilities powered by R.

projects.title: Budget Minder
projects.description: Automate document submission within a school.Budget Minder is a web-based application designed to help users manage and forecast their monthly budgets. Users can input their income and expenses, set savings goals, and track their progress.

projects.title: Fine-Tuning EfficientNet for Medical Image Classification
projects.description: The project will be directed towards the development of a robust medical image classifier using the state-of-the-art convolutional neural network architecture known as EfficientNet.

projects.title: TBE
projects.description: A multi-language toolkit for handling TBE (Tabular Data with Metadata Blocks and Enrichment) files. This suite includes libraries in Python, C, Rust, R, JavaScript, and Java, designed for flexible use by both programmers and data analysts.
